HEADWORD: jitterbug
<hw>jitterbug</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a fast and vigorous American dance
that was popular in the 1940s, having few standardized steps and
personalized with various twirls, twists, and acrobatic moves; it was
performed often to the accompaniment of swing or boogie-woogie
tunes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

